From: gt-be98 open-driver RE
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] brcmfmac: add chip-id + pcie device-id defines for BCM6717/6726

Adds the chip-common IDs and placeholder PCIe device-IDs for the GT-BE98
FullMAC radios. The chip IDs are confirmed from dhd.ko strings/firmware dirs
(6717a0, 6726b0; 6715/43684 also referenced in the same family).

The PCIe device-IDs are PLACEHOLDERS: the on-device dhd driver matches by PCI
*class* (0x028000 / mask 0x00ffff00) with PCI_ANY_ID for the device field, so
the true config-space device-id was never pinned by RE. They must be confirmed
on the bench (read PCI config 0x02 of the radio function). Values below are the
documented Broadcom 6717/6726 EHT-family IDs as a starting point.

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/include/brcm_hw_ids.h
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/include/brcm_hw_ids.h
@@ -61,6 +61,11 @@
 #define BRCM_CC_4371_CHIP_ID		0x4371
+/* GT-BE98 FullMAC (dhd) radios — WiFi-7 / 802.11be family.
+ * Confirmed present from on-device firmware dirs: 6717a0, 6726b0.
+ */
+#define BRCM_CC_6715_CHIP_ID		0x6715
+#define BRCM_CC_6717_CHIP_ID		0x6717
+#define BRCM_CC_6726_CHIP_ID		0x6726
 #define CY_CC_4373_CHIP_ID		0x4373
@@ -92,3 +92,8 @@
 #define BRCM_PCIE_4371_DEVICE_ID	0x440d
+/* PLACEHOLDER device-ids — dhd matches by class, not devid; confirm on bench. */
+#define BRCM_PCIE_6715_DEVICE_ID	0x6715
+#define BRCM_PCIE_6717_DEVICE_ID	0x6717
+#define BRCM_PCIE_6726_DEVICE_ID	0x6726
